# Fix Frontend Build Error: Restore `generateReportPdf`

The frontend build failed because `src/pages/Reports.tsx` attempts to import `generateReportPdf` from `src/lib/corporatePdf.ts`, but this function was missing. This plan restores the function while updating it to match the new monochrome corporate design system.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component: PDF Library]

#### [MODIFY] [corporatePdf.ts](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/src/lib/corporatePdf.ts)

- Re-introduce `ReportPdfData` interface based on usage in `Reports.tsx`.
- Re-introduce `generateReportPdf` function.
- Update the restored function to use the new `drawHeader` and monochrome `BRAND` palette.
- Implement the `hexToRgb` helper for leave type distribution bars.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run build` locally in the project root to ensure the import error is resolved.
- Re-run the deployment script `.\deploy-posh.ps1 -SkipConfirm`.

### Manual Verification
- Test the "Export PDF" button in the Analytics dashboard once deployed.
